    6.3.2 Programmable Notch Filter (NF)

The NAU88C10 has a programmable notch filter which passes all frequencies except those in a stop band centered on
a given center frequency. The filter gives lower distortion and flattens response. The notch filter is enabled by setting
NFCEN[7] address (0x1B) to HIGH. The variable center frequency is programmed by setting two’s complement values
to NFCA0[6:0] address (0x1C), NFCA0[13:7] address (0x1B) and NFCA1[6:0] address (0x1E), NFCA1[13:7] address
(0x1D) registers. The coefficients are updated in the circuit when the NFCU[8] bit is set HIGH in a write to any of the
registers NF1-NF4 address (0x1B, 0x1C, 0x1D, 0x1E).

