The DAC digital block uses 24-bit signal processing to generate analog audio using data from the audio data bus or
from the ADC output. This block consists of a sigma-delta modulator, 5-band graphic equalizer, high pass filter, digital
gain/filters, de-emphasis, and analog mixers. The DAC coding scheme is in twos complement format and the full-scale
output level is proportional to VDDA. With a 3.3V supply voltage, the full-scale output level is 1.0VRMS. The DAC is
enabled by setting DACEN[0] address (0x03) bit HIGH.

