    6.6.1 Speaker Mixer Outputs

The speaker amplifiers are designed to drive a load differentially; a configuration referred to as Bridge-Tied Load (BTL).
The differential speaker outputs can drive a single 8Ω speaker or two headphone loads of 16Ω or higher, including
differential line output applications. Driving the load differentially doubles the output voltage. The output of the speaker
can be manipulated by changing attenuation and the volume (loudness of the output signal).

