 6.9.1.2 2-WIRE Write Operation

A Write operation consists of a two-byte instruction followed by one or more Data Bytes. A Write operation requires a
START condition, followed by a valid device address byte, a valid control address byte, data byte(s), and a STOP
condition. After each three bytes sequence, the NAU88C10 responds with an ACK and the 2-Wire interface enters a
standby state.

