6.23 PCM Time Slot Control & ADCOUT Impedance Option Control

 6.23.1 PCM1 Timeslot Control Register

Addr   D8     D7          D6        D5          D4          D3        D2      D1      D0 Default

0x3B                                            TSLOT[8:0]                            0x000

Transmit and receive timeslot are expressed in number of BCLK cycles in a 10-bit word. The most significant bit
TSLOT[9] is located in register PCMTS2[0] address (0x3C). Timeslot, TSLOT[9:0], determines the start point for the
timeslot on the PCM interface for data in the transmit direction.

6.23.2 PCM2 Timeslot Control Register

Addr   D8             D7  D6        D5          D4          D3        D2      D1      D0 Default

0x3C PCMTSEN TRI PCM8BIT PUDOEN PUDPE PUDPS LOUTR PCMB TSLOT[9] 0x000

                          PUDPE

                             PUDPS                                    ADCOUT
                          iADCOUT

                             PUDOE

Name    PCM Transit          Tri-state PCMT     PCM Word Length       Left and Right  PCM Mode2
  Bit       Enable                  LSB                               Channel have       PCMB
   0                                                PCM8BIT[6]                           Disable
   1   PCMTSEN[8]                  TRI[7]                               same data        Enable
                                                Use WLEN[6:5] to          LOUTR
           PCM A          Drive the full Clock  select Word Length
                          of LSB                Audio interface will      Disable
       PCM Time Slot                            be 8 Bit Word
                          Tri-State the 2nd     Length                    Enable
                          half of LSB

If TRI = 1 and PUDOEN = 0, the device will drive the LSB bit 1st half of BCLK out of the ADCOUT pin (stop driving
after LSB BCLK Rising edge) but if TRI = 0 or PUDOEN = 1 this feature is disabled, full BCLK of LSB will be driven
the LSB value.

